20 Section 2. The legislature recognizes the importance of empowering those
21 individuals who are victims of sex offenses and the need to protect their privacy and
22 personal information from disclosure. It is therefore the intent of the legislature to enact
23 statutory provisions to limit public access to personal information of victims of sex offenses
24 and to provide for legal consequences for the unauthorized release of this information. This
25 Act shall be known and may be cited as the "Sexual Assault Survivor Empowerment and
26 Privacy Protection Act."
